{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44a1a29d-6d26-417f-a253-73717c0f4c63","content":"The issue is classic F# — **file compilation order matters**. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on types defined in `Domain.fs`. F# compiles files top-to-bottom as listed.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01EicU2biywawA7uLyP4mLn5","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Fixing F# file order"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MvPXtXU8qVWx1w65WETbSy","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-664c9d8d289045dea207639911a89656/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-664c9d8d289045dea207639911a89656/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"aedfd8ab-bf3c-41c9-8b49-0182ab22a800","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs - depends on Domain.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain)\n2. Domain.fs - defines the types\n3. Program.fs - depends on both\n\nServices.fs is listed before Domain.fs, but Services.fs depends on Domain.fs. The fix is to reorder so Domain.fs comes first.\n\nCorrect order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":429,"requestId":"D815:3D7DF2:6A94A8E:72E362D:6A03CC46"},"id":"058ec2e0-b1cf-44ad-986f-d63ca2a30987","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:56:46.397Z","parentId":"e76c1219-0c74-433a-bd3c-b28429c7a160"}
